msgstr ""

#: ../../src/user/nodes-system/managing-nodes.rst:180
msgid "**Draft**: First status for new nodes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/user/nodes-system/managing-nodes.rst:181
msgid "**Pending validation**: It’s a medium status for user that do not have permission to publish nodes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/user/nodes-system/managing-nodes.rst:182
msgid "**Published**: That’s the most important status, it will set the green light to your visitor to view your content"
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/user/nodes-system/managing-nodes.rst:183
msgid "**Archived**: When you don’t want to publish a node but you don’t want to delete it either"
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/user/nodes-system/managing-nodes.rst:184
msgid "**Deleted**: It’s the last status for your nodes. Before emptying your node trashcan, every content will wait with this status."
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/user/nodes-system/managing-nodes.rst:186
msgid "To improve status visibility, *draft* and *pending* nodes have a rhombus shape and *published* nodes have a circle shape."
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/user/nodes-system/managing-nodes.rst:189
msgid "Preview unpublished nodes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/user/nodes-system/managing-nodes.rst:191
msgid "As unpublished nodes are not viewable for anonymous visitors, Roadiz allows backend users to preview them using a dedicated *entry point* called ``preview.php``, yes this is not very original. We decided to create a different entry point not to share the same URL with your public website as it could create confusing errors if your website is hosted behing a reverse proxy engine."
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/user/nodes-system/managing-nodes.rst:196
msgid "For example, if your ``my-news`` page is not published yet, connecting to ``http://mywebsite.com/my-news`` will lead to a 404 page for your anonymous visitors, as well as you too. If you want to preview it, you’ll have to connect to ``http://mywebsite.com/preview.php/my-news``. This URL will only allow authentified backend users, other people will be blocked."
msgstr ""

